<A NAME=POEM2></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>
sheen of apples&nbsp;&#8212;
<br>
in a migrant child&#8217;s lap
<br>
her own dirty feet
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Andrew Riutta
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM4></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>
my mother braiding my hair . . .
<br>
I realize now
<br>
how young she was
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Bonnie Stepenoff
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM6></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>
walking alone&nbsp;&#8212;
<br>
my face
<br>
disassembles
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Hilary Tann
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM8></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>
rushing home
<br>
as though you were still there
<br>
autumn dusk
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Dru Philippou
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM10></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>
autumn leaves
<br>
the songs we learn                      
<br>
as children
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
jennie townsend
